Note:
TYPE LOWERING - HIR Types to MIR Type Metadata (P2-E Group B)

Per the CEO full-coverage mandate, every HIR_* node type
(10000-14999) must have a registered handler so dispatch
coverage is 100%. HIR type nodes (13000-13014) carry compile-
time type information consumed by codegen via the type-table
pathway; they do NOT lower to runtime MIR instructions.

This module installs post-only handlers for every HIR type
node. Each handler is a documented no-op marker that records
the type was visited (no MIR emission). When the MIR program's
type_table field is wired through, these handlers will populate
it with the resolved type metadata.

Nodes handled (15 total):
  HIR_BASIC_TYPE         (13000)
  HIR_GENERIC_TYPE       (13001)
  HIR_UNION_TYPE         (13002)
  HIR_INTERSECTION_TYPE  (13003)
  HIR_FUNCTION_TYPE      (13004)
  HIR_OPTIONAL_TYPE      (13005)
  HIR_ARRAY_TYPE         (13006)
  HIR_TUPLE_TYPE         (13007)
  HIR_RECORD_TYPE        (13008)
  HIR_TYPE_PARAMETER     (13009)
  HIR_TYPE_CONSTRAINT    (13010)
  HIR_REFERENCE_TYPE     (13011)
  HIR_POINTER_TYPE       (13012)
  HIR_SLICE_TYPE         (13013)
  HIR_NEVER_TYPE         (13014)
:End Note

Note: ============================================================
Note: IMPORTS
Note: ============================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/lowering/lowering_context.runa" as LCtx

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_BASIC_TYPE post handler (13000)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_BASIC_TYPE post: primitive types (Integer, Float, String,
Boolean, etc.). The visitor walks into a type node only when a
parent expression or declaration references it. No runtime MIR
emission is needed; the type is consumed by codegen via the
type-table pathway. The handler is a marker for dispatch
coverage and a future hook for type-table population.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads the type kind at HIR_BASIC_TYPE offset 0 for diagnostic
purposes only; emits nothing. Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline. Hot path for any
expression with a typed result (effectively every expression in
typed code).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation. Defensive null check.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_basic_type_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_GENERIC_TYPE post handler (13001)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_GENERIC_TYPE post: a generic instantiation (e.g.,
List[Integer]). The generic parameters have already been visited
by the visitor's variadic walk per the v3 design Section 4.1;
this handler just acknowledges the parent generic type was seen.
Future monomorphization will use this hook to record instantiations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_generic_type_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_UNION_TYPE post handler (13002)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_UNION_TYPE post: union type (A OR B). The variant types
have already been visited; the union itself is metadata. Runtime
representation (tagged union) is generated by codegen based on
the type-table entry, not at lowering time.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_union_type_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_INTERSECTION_TYPE post handler (13003)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_INTERSECTION_TYPE post: intersection type (A AND B). The
component types have been visited. Runtime representation is a
structural composition of the components, generated by codegen
based on the type-table entry.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_intersection_type_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_FUNCTION_TYPE post handler (13004)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_FUNCTION_TYPE post: function signature type. Parameter
types and return type have been visited as children. The
function-type metadata is consumed by call-site lowering and
function-pointer lowering; no MIR emission is needed here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

