Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_POINTER_TYPE post handler (13012)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_POINTER_TYPE post: raw pointer type (*T). Used in FFI and
unsafe code. Inner type is visited as a child. Lowers to a
pointer value at MIR; the handler is a metadata marker.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation. Raw pointers bypass borrow checking; the HIR
layer enforces unsafe-block containment.
@End Security_Scope

