Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_NEVER_TYPE post handler (13014)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_NEVER_TYPE post: the bottom type (!). Used for functions
that never return (panic, exit, infinite loops). No runtime
representation; the type system uses it to mark unreachable
control flow. The handler is purely a marker.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

